** Company Description **

** Every institution values excellence. What matters most is why. **   
Griffith was created to be a different type of university. You’ll find we’re
about leading research, academic excellence, and the transformative power of
education. But what sets us apart is why those things matter and how you’ll
achieve them.

** Why? ** Griffith brings together exceptional minds like yours from across the globe and from all walks of life. Here, we do incredible work, questioning and challenging, always in the pursuit of excellence. 

** Digital Solutions. A team you’ll want to be a part of. **

When you join Digital Solutions, you’ll be part of a team that delivers impact
by enhancing digital experiences for the graduates of tomorrow, researchers of
today and all those working to make it a brighter future.

But we know it’s not just what you do that matters, it’s who you do it with.
Our people will tell you – our team sets us apart. We promise a supportive and
friendly environment where you’ll collaborate to make an impact.

Make it matter. Join Digital Solutions at Griffith.

** Job Description **

** About the opportunity **

This is an exciting time to join our team where you will be supported to
develop your skills and stay on trend with emerging techniques and technology.
Reporting to the Information Solutions Lead, use your experience developing
technology solutions to solve information management problems and streamline
business processes.

Explore the challenges faced by colleagues across corporate, research and
teaching areas and develop solutions using a range of technology tools such as
Microsoft 365/Power Platform, Acrobat Sign and AvePoint’s governance suite to
solve them. Use your analysis skills to understand requirements and design
appropriate solutions that can range from basic SharePoint Online site
configuration through to complex workflows, digital forms, and dashboards.

Contribute to the management of our new M365 governance tool through user
support and the development of new automated services and processes and
provide advice to a variety of stakeholders and colleagues, with the objective
of educating how utilising technology and digital IM techniques can improve
their processes.

** About you **

  * Experience in developing solutions using the M365 suite including SharePoint Online and the Power Platform (Power Apps, Power Automate, Power BI) 
  * Ability to work independently, prioritise and manage multiple competing tasks while delivering solutions through all stages through to completion 
  * Demonstrated skills and experience in digital information management and governance 
  * Creativity, problem solving and business analysis skills 
  * Excellent interpersonal skills and the ability to liaise with various types of stakeholders 
  * A background in IT, preferred but not essential. 

Your qualifications should include demonstrated work experience, education and
training in the fields of systems design and development, business process
improvement, information management or information governance equivalent to:

  * An undergraduate degree with at least 2 years' subsequent relevant experience; or 
  * 5 years of relevant work experience and expertise in the fields mentioned above 
  * an equivalent combination of relevant experience and/or education/training. 

Applicants must have unrestricted work rights and may be subject to a criminal
history check.

** What we can offer **   
  
This is a fixed term, full-time position until 31/12/24 based at our Nathan
campus. As Griffith is a multi-site University you may be required to work
across other campuses.

The full time equivalent base salary will be HEW Level 7 range $93,854 -
$101,680 per annum + 17% superannuation. The total FTE package will be in the
range $109,809 - $118,966 per annum.

** Additional Information **

** Why join Griffith? **   
  
As a values-led organisation, at Griffith University, we've worked hard to
create a dynamic and strong organisational culture. We offer:

  * Wide range of Learning and Development opportunities 
  * Mix of on campus and work from home options available and a supportive work environment 
  * Salary packaging options and corporate health discounts 
  * Generous leave entitlements including paid parental leave and leave loading 
  * Support with future learning opportunities through our educational staff assistance scheme 
  * Opportunities for internal mobility 
  * Health Safety and Wellbeing initiatives – on campus Gym facilities 

At Griffith, we’re committed to providing a safe and inclusive environment for
all - whoever you are and wherever you’re from. If you require any
accommodations, we welcome you to let us know so we can work with you to
participate fully in our recruitment experience.

Griffith University values diversity, inclusion and flexibility and we
encourage Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander, and people of all backgrounds
to apply. For more information please visit our [ Equity, Diversity and
Inclusion ](https://www.griffith.edu.au/equity#:~:text=At%20Griffith%20we%20un
derstand%20that,safe%2C%20supportive%20and%20productive%20environment) page.
Griffith University also maintains a strict zero-tolerance policy against all
forms of modern slavery. For more information, please refer to Griffith’s [
Modern Slavery Policy
](https://www.griffith.edu.au/__data/assets/pdf_file/0037/1687357/modern-
slavery-policy-2022.pdf) .

